## What is Cloud?
Cloud means running applications on remote servers on the internet instead of your own computer.

Example:
Instead of running app on your laptop
You run it on a server that anyone can access via internet

## What is AWS?

AWS (Amazon Web Services) is a cloud platform that provides:
Virtual servers
Databases
Storage
Networking

## What is EC2?

EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud) is a virtual computer in the cloud.
It is used to:
Run Spring Boot application
Host backend services
Make app available on internet

## What is RDS?
RDS (Relational Database Service) is a managed cloud database service.

Used to:
Host MySQL / PostgreSQL / etc in cloud
Avoid installing database on server manually

## Real Project Architecture
User Browser
    ↓
EC2 (Spring Boot Application)
    ↓
RDS (MySQL Database)

## What is JAR?

JAR is a packaged Java application file that contains:
Your code
Dependencies
Configurations

## How Spring Boot is Deployed 

Build jar:
mvn clean package
Create EC2 server
Install Java on EC2
Upload jar file

Run:
java -jar app.jar

Access app:
http://ec2-ip:8080

## Database Configuration

In production, we use:
AWS RDS instead of local DB

Change in application.properties:
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://rds-endpoint:3306/db
spring.datasource.username=admin
spring.datasource.password=pass

## Interview Answers
What is cloud?
Cloud means running applications on remote servers over internet.

What is AWS?
AWS is Amazon’s cloud platform.

What is EC2?
EC2 is a virtual server in AWS used to run applications.

What is RDS?
RDS is a managed cloud database service.

How did you deploy your project?
I built a jar using Maven and deployed it on AWS EC2. Database was hosted on AWS RDS.
